{"title_page": "Tjernsrud (station)", "text_new": "{{Short description|Former Oslo metro station}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name                = Tjernsrud\n| style               = \n| image               = Tjernsrud.jpg\n| image_caption       = [[OS T1000|T1300]] train departing Tjernsrud in 2006\n| address             = [[B\u00e6rum]],\n| country             = [[Norway]]\n| coordinates         = {{Coord|59.9208|10.6106|region:NO_type:railwaystation|display=inline,title}}\n| elevation           = \n| line                = [[Kols\u00e5s Line]]<br>[[Lilleaker Line]]\n| connections         = \n| distance            = {{convert|9.1|km|abbr=on}} \n| structure           = At-grade\n| platform            = \n| depth               = \n| levels              = \n| tracks              = \n| parking             = \n| bicycle             = \n| opened              = 1 July 1924\n| closed              = 2009\n| rebuilt             = \n| ADA                 = \n| code                = \n| owned               =\n| operator            =\n| zone                = \n| smartcardname       = \n| smartcardstatus     = \n| former              = \n| passengers          = \n| pass_year           = \n| pass_percent        = \n| pass_system         = \n| mpassengers         = \n| services            = \n}}\n\n'''Tjernsrud''' was a [[rapid transit station|station]] on the [[Kols\u00e5s Line]] (line 6) on the [[Oslo Metro]] system. Located in [[B\u00e6rum]], [[Norway]], it was between [[Ringstabekk (old station)|Ringstabekk]] and [[Jar (station)|Jar]], 9.9&nbsp;km west of [[Stortinget (station)|Stortinget]]. It served the neighborhoods of northern [[Stabekk]] and southeastern [[Jar, Norway|Jar]].\n\nThe station was opened on 1 July 1924 as part of the tramway [[Lilleaker Line|B\u00e6rum Line]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sporveien.no/templates/Page____1033.aspx |author=[[Oslo Sporveier]] |title=Subway stations in the west}}</ref>\n\nAlong with most of the line, Tjernsrud was closed for upgrades since 1 July 2006. From August 2007 its service was temporarily provided by tram line 13, as an extension of the service from Jar to [[Bekkestua (station)|Bekkestua]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sporveien.no/templates/page____1150.aspx |title=Bus replacing the Kols\u00e5s line |author=Oslo Sporveier |language=Norwegian |date=2006}}</ref> It was decided not to reopen Tjernsrud as a metro station, and as the tram service ended in February 2009, it was demolished soon after.\n\nThe company responsible for public transport in Oslo, [[Ruter]], has the long-term objective of opening the [[Kols\u00e5s Line]] for Metro use again.\n\n[[File:Tjernsrud demolished.jpg|thumb|left|Tjernsrud station in a demolished state, April 2009.]]\n{{Clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Oslo Metro}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tjernsrud (Station)}}\n[[Category:Oslo Metro stations in B\u00e6rum]]\n[[Category:Oslo Tramway stations in B\u00e6rum]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 1924]]\n[[Category:Railway stations closed in 2009]]\n[[Category:Disused Oslo Metro stations]]\n[[Category:1924 establishments in Norway]]\n[[Category:2009 disestablishments in Norway]]\n\n\n{{Oslo-metro-stub}}\n{{Norway-tram-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|Former Oslo metro station}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name                = Tjernsrud\n| style               = \n| image               = Tjernsrud.jpg\n| image_caption       = [[OS T1000|T1300]] train departing Tjernsrud in 2006\n| address             = [[B\u00e6rum]],\n| country             = [[Norway]]\n| coordinates         = {{Coord|59.9208|10.6106|region:NO_type:railwaystation|display=inline,title}}\n| elevation           = \n| line                = [[Kols\u00e5s Line]]<br>[[Lilleaker Line]]\n| connections         = \n| distance            = {{convert|9.1|km|abbr=on}} \n| structure           = At-grade\n| platform            = \n| depth               = \n| levels              = \n| tracks  